{
  "$schema": "../schemas/Causal-Decision-Model.json",
  "meta": {
    "uuid": "a3ff4c05-eaf7-4891-92a1-ea9a5848c4f3",
    "name": "SKEL-04: Demand Forecasting",
    "summary": "Canonical skeleton for demand forecasting. Five Levers, six Externals, six Intermediates, four Outcomes. 40 causal dependencies.",
    "documentation": {
      "content": "KODI Lite \u00b7 SKEL-04 \u00b7 Demand Forecasting\n\nLevers (5): Forecast Horizon, Forecast Method, Segmentation Granularity, Consensus Adjustment Weight, Forecast Review Frequency\nExternals (6): Historical Sales Volume, Demand Seasonality Index, Market Price Index, Competitor Activity Index, Macroeconomic Indicator, Promotional Event Calendar\nIntermediates (6): Statistical Baseline Forecast [I1 = w1*E1 + w2*E2 - w3*E3 + w4*E5 + w5*E6 + w6*A2 - w7*A1 + b], Forecast Bias [I2 = w1*A4 - w2*A5 + w3*E4 + b], Demand Volatility [I3 = w1*E4 + w2*E3 + w3*E6 - w4*E1 + b], Consensus Forecast [I4 = w1*I1 + w2*A4 - w3*I2 + w4*A5 + b], Forecast Accuracy [I5 = -w1*I3 + w2*A2 + w3*A3 + w4*A5 - w5*I2 + b], Forecast Confidence Interval [I6 = w1*I3 - w2*I5 + w3*A1 + b]\nOutcomes (4): Demand Plan Quality [maximise], Inventory Implication [minimise], Revenue Forecast Confidence [maximise], Excess Stock Exposure [minimise]",
      "MIMEType": "text/plain"
    },
    "version": "1.0",
    "draft": false,
    "createdDate": "2026-07-01T09:00:00Z"
  },
